## Cedar( object )
Create a new chart using an object that can include specification from a template, dataset and mappings, and style overrides.  This is optional and any of the parameters can be later specified through accessors. 

The chart will not appear until `Cedar.show` is called.

`new Cedar(options)`

#### Arguments

| Name | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `options.specification` | <`string | object`> | no | URL to a Vega extended template or an inline Vega object. |
| `options.dataset` | <`object`> | no | Hash of layer URL and field to input mappings as required by the `specification`. |
| `options.override` | <`object`> | no | Object that is merged with the `specification.template` for runtime styling. |


### Examples

```
var chart = new Cedar({"specification":"{{assets}}data/templates/bar-chart-template.json"});

//create the dataset w/ mappings
var dataset = {
  "url":"http://maps2.dcgis.dc.gov/dcgis/rest/services/DCGIS_DATA/Education_WebMercator/MapServer/5",
  "mappings":{
    "group": {"field":"ZIP_CODE","label":"ZIP Code"},
    "count": {"field":"TOTAL_STUD","label":"Total Students"}
  }
};

//assign to the chart
chart.dataset = dataset;


// make the chart visible by attaching it to a DOM node
chart.show({
  elementId: "#chart"
});
```